																					<p>Hello MS Students!</p>

																					<p>Wow, do we certainly miss you all and hope that you are all safe, healthy, engaged in learning, and practicing the always important social distancing!</p>

																					<p>Below is important information regarding upcoming days and other MS news:</p>

																					<p>May 8th - NO SCHOOL. Enjoy another day off! You earned it!</p>

																					<p>May 18th - ALL assignments, work and projects must be completed by this date unless previously discussed with your teacher.  We appreciate all of the hard work and effort that many of you are putting in during remote learning. This May 18th deadline for all work gives our teachers time to grade assignments and leads to our next bit of news that we think you might enjoy…</p>

																					<p>NO FINAL EXAMS!!!!!!!! This being said, WE WILL STILL HAVE CLASSES FOR REMOTE LEARNING from 5/18 to 5/22 with assignments that will have grades. This work will be due within 48 hours of the class period. This gift of no final exams allows you the opportunity to check in with your teachers, make sure all assignments are completed and submitted, and to get extra help on any late work when you would typically be studying for finals. </p>

																					<p>Have a great day!</p>

																					<p>Mr. Dittrich and Mr. Flores</p>

																					<p> </p>
